-- Vakifbank to Offer as Much as $2 Billion of Debt
-- B y   S e l c u k   G o k o l u k
-- 2012-07-21T12:45:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-21/vakifbank-to-offer-as-much-as-2-billion-of-debt.html
Turkiye Vakiflar Bankasi TAO, a
state-run bank, applied to Turkey’s market regulator to offer a
maximum $2 billion of debt with a minimum two-year maturity.  Vakifbank’s bonds will be denominated in dollars, euros,
Swiss francs and other currencies with “high liquidity” in
international markets, the lender said in a statement to the
 Istanbul Stock Exchange  after the market closed yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Selcuk Gokoluk in Istanbul at 
